entry.title: As Ukraine Readies Counteroffensive, Russia Steps Up Campaign Against Partisans
entry.content: Russia is deepening a crackdown on dissent in occupied areas of Ukraine, the Ukrainian military said, as Kyiv’s forces launched fresh attacks aimed at weakening Moscow’s hold in the south.

entry.content: Army doctors and medics practice skills and relay combat lessons to trauma units.

entry.title: Israel's Efforts to Expand Arab Relations Slow Over Recent Turmoil
entry.content: Middle East governments are lodging complaints over conflict with Palestinians and Netanyahu’s far-right coalition.

entry.title: East Palestine Isn't Alone. How One Town Recovered From a Toxic Train Derailment.
entry.content: Paulsboro, N.J., residents have worked to move past a vinyl chloride release a decade ago that raised health concerns and hit businesses and housing.
